In [24]:
def make_features(data, max_lag, rolling_mean_size):
    data_copy = data.copy()
#     data_copy['year'] = data_copy.index.year #      
#     data_copy['month'] = data_copy.index.month
    data_copy['day'] = data_copy.index.day
    data_copy['dayofweek'] = data_copy.index.dayofweek
    data_copy['hour'] = data_copy.index.hour
    
    for lag in range(1, max_lag + 1):
        data_copy['lag_{}'.format(lag)] = data_copy['num_orders'].shift(lag)

    data_copy['rolling_mean'] = data_copy['num_orders'].shift().rolling(rolling_mean_size).mean()
    return data_copy

def features_target_separator(data, target_name):
    target = data[target_name]
    features = data.drop(columns=target_name)
    return features, target

#      GridSearchCV

def pipeline_gridsearchcv(X, y, steps, params
#                           , scoring
                          , verbose = 1):
    
    #   pipeline 
    pipe = Pipeline(steps)
 
    #   ,  
    grid = GridSearchCV(pipe, param_grid=params
                        , cv= ts_cv #    3  5, ,  shuffle=False
                        , n_jobs=-1
                        , scoring='neg_root_mean_squared_error' #RMSE
                        , verbose=verbose
                        , error_score='raise')
    grid.fit(X, y)
    
#     #   
#     display('')
#     display('  :', grid.best_params_)
#     display('   :', -grid.best_score_)
    
    return grid
